+{"id":"frankenjax-pzj4","title":"Conv trace shape inference panics on zero 2D stride","description":"[HIGH] crates/fj-trace/src/lib.rs Conv shape inference parses params["strides"] into usize values but does not reject zero in the rank-4 path. Repro: create a SimpleTraceContext with lhs ShapedArray { dtype: F64, shape: [1,3,3,1] } and rhs ShapedArray { dtype: F64, shape: [1,1,1,1] }, then call process_primitive(Primitive::Conv, &[lhs_id, rhs_id], params) with padding="same" and strides="0,1" or "0,0". Expected: Err(TraceError::InvalidPrimitiveParam or ShapeInferenceFailed) matching fj-lax runtime stride validation. Actual: the 2D path assigns stride_h=0 at lines around 1490-1492, then SAME padding reaches height.div_ceil(stride_h) around line 1522 and panics in debug/test builds. The 1D path also uses strides[0].max(1), silently accepting strides="0" instead of rejecting it, so the fix should share strict positive stride parsing across 1D and 2D trace inference and add regression tests for 1D zero stride and 2D zero height/width stride.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T14:43:56.265914430Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T14:43:56.265914430Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
